&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Colorectal /Stoma Care Enhanced Recovery Nurse Specialist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6- 37.5 hrs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic, motivated and proactive individual who is open to learning and working within a progressive established team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; You should have experience of caring for patients with colorectal disease and with a particular interest in enhanced recovery after surgery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You need to possess excellent communication and interpersonal skills. A commitment to providing a high quality service and Ensure commitment to working in partnership with patients, their families &amp; other providers so they feel in control of their health and care needs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post presents an excellent opportunity to be involved in colorectal and enhanced recovery specialist care pre and post-surgery. Working within multi-varied case loads. You will also need to work independently and as part of a specialised team. Promoting nursing excellence in best practice, patient centred care, nurse led initiatives and empowerment for patients and their families. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are committed to delivering the highest quality and safest treatment and care to every patient every time. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An understanding of the needs of the client group is essential. This post will require the successful candidate to undertake further study within Colorectal/ Enhanced Recovery and Oncology post registration qualifications.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are dedicated to providing a supportive working environment, enabling the successful individual to progress within this role with opportunities for further education for professional and personal development. Learning opportunities will be available based on the needs of the individual.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For further information please contact: Julie Hemingway (CNS Nurse Specialist Manager), Sammy Limbert (Colorectal/ Enhanced Recovery Nurse Specialist) on 0113 20-65535/ 64225 or Matron, Linda Johnson on 0113 2068265.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
